IMPRESSION:
1.  Slightly increased size of a left suboccipital-C2 paraspinal schwannoma which follows the expected course of the greater occipital nerve. No mass effect on the thecal sac. Partially included portion in the left C1 to foramen.
2.  There are 2 small schwannomas in the left periauricular soft tissues which are increased in size compared to June 2021.
3.  No acute intracranial abnormality. Specifically no intracranial schwannomas identified.
4.  See separately dictated concurrently obtained MRI brachial plexus.
